# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Runtime auth state — sessions are live, non-expiring bearer tokens,
# never version-controlled. users.json IS committed (see below the divider)
# — the app has no seeding/bootstrap path, so a deploy with no users.json
# means load_users() returns [] and every login 401s regardless of
# credentials (root cause of a production login outage on 2026-07-22).
# The demo accounts' shared password is already public on the Login page
# itself (dashboard-react/src/lib/auth/demoAccounts.js), so the hashes in
# users.json don't protect a real secret — safe to ship.
data/sessions.json

# Pure performance cache (agents/translation_agent.py's LLM translations,
# keyed by content hash) — unlike incidents/notifications/tasks this holds
# no meaningful seed data, only regenerable derived output. Missing on a
# fresh deploy is a harmless no-op (translation_cache_store.load() returns
# {}), not an outage like the users.json lesson above.
data/translation_cache.json
